# Readingnotes-03

# VCM
> - Any commited change is refered as a snapshot
> - Usually rely on local operations to function correctly
> - Applications like git track changes that are made to it
> - This method helps losing or corrupting files
> - Easily clone and import
> - You can hide any changes from the commit by stashing them
> - Easy to work with multiple repositories
> - You can clone a repositories
